  "texts": [
    "Therefore, it can generate each observation x n considering its previous history x 1:n-1.",
    "However, GAN-based generative models are vulnerable to the issue of mode collapse [27] and unstable behavior problems during training [28].",
    "GT-GAN [7] attempted to solve the problems by incorporating an invertible neural networkbased generator into its framework.",
    "There also exist GANbased methods to generate other types of sequential data, e.g., video, sound, etc [29]- [32].",
    "In our experiments, we also use them as our baselines for thorough evaluations."
  ]
